    <text id="F3508T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>John Reed requests the paperwork necessary to obtain a leave of absence.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">L. Thomas, Ajt. General</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-01-31">January 31, 1863</date>
                        <name type="place">Johnstown</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Dear">Dr.</abbr> Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Enclosed I leave fi<del rend="none" hand="h1"/>ed certificate of disability from my attending
                    Physician who is medical examiner of the county in care of those applying for
                    pensions. My first leave was for twenty days commencing Decemebr 23/62, on
                    account of wounds received at Fredericksburg. As by <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>ion of and
                    issued by L. Thomas, Adjutant General.</p>

                <p>I sent over my <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> at the expiration of the first twenty days one
                    copy to L. Thomas, Ajt. General, and one copy to <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> Col. of 126
                    Regt. In a letter received by three or four days after the Col. acknowledged the
                    receipt of my papers. But I have not heard from the Ajt. general, and fear the
                    papers may have been lost or overlooked. Please send over all the necessary
                    papers for this and the former ones sent by <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> from this place
                        <abbr expan="January">Jany.</abbr> 11th, 1862.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>I am very Respectfully<lb/> Your Obedient Servant</salute>
                    <signed>John Reed</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
